```python
def load_data(filename):
    infile = open(filename, 'rb')
    return pickle.load(infile)
```

```python
def sync_data(state_list, result_type, stats_dict, stats_df):

    state_err = {}

    for state in state_list:
        #test = list(us_IC_df[us_IC_df[state] > 0][state])
        test = list(stats_df[state])
        test_len = len(test)
        lowest_err = {}
        ref_err = {}

        for conf_trig in stats_dict[result_type]:
            check_rms = None
            test_model_col = test
            test_mean_refa = list(stats_dict[result_type][conf_trig]['mean'])
            test_mean_ref = list(np.zeros(60))
            for i in range(len(test_mean_refa)):
                test_mean_ref.append(test_mean_refa[i])
            for x in range(len(test_mean_ref)-test_len):
                xx = x + test_len
                test_mean_col = test_mean_ref[x:xx]
                test_rms = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(test_model_col, test_mean_col))
                if check_rms == None or test_rms < check_rms:
                    check_rms = test_rms
                    check_col = test_mean_col
                    check_start = x
            lowest_err[conf_trig] = {'mean': check_col, 'real': test_model_col, 'mean long': test_mean_ref[check_start:]}
        state_err[state] = lowest_err
    
    return state_err
```


```python
state_err_IC = sync_data(state_list, 'IC', stats_dict, us_IC_df)
```

## Interactive Plots Displaying Up-to-date State Statistics Against Ensemble Model Results
### First Plot: US State Confirmed Infectious Reports Plotted Against Truncated Ensemble Model Means
The truncated plots allow for closer inspection of the results of the different ensemble means compared against the reported confirmed cases.


```python
fig, cx = plt.subplots(1, figsize=(9,5))


def update_plot_1(input_1, input_2):
    
    beh_max_list = list(stats_dict['S'].keys())
    cx.clear()
    for inp in input_1:
        
        state = input_2

        inpa = properties_dict['Model Sets'][inp]['id']
        
        y = state_err_IC[state][inpa]['real']
        yy = state_err_IC[state][inpa]['mean']
               
        cx.set_title(f'{input_2} Reported Confirmed Infectious Statistics\nSynchronized against Ensemble Means')
        lgnd = f'{input_1}'
        cx.set_xlabel('Day (starting 1 Feb 2020)')
        cx.set_ylabel('Total per 10,000 Population')
        lgnd_set = plt.gca().get_legend_handles_labels()[1]
        cx.plot(y, color='k', linewidth=3, label=f'{state} Data' if f'{state} Data' not in lgnd_set else '')
        cx.plot(yy, label= inp[20:] if inp[20:] not in lgnd_set else '')
        cx.legend(loc=2)


beh_mod_wid = widgets.SelectMultiple(options=properties_dict['Model Sets'].keys(), value=list(properties_dict['Model Sets']), description='Ensemble')
state_wid = widgets.ToggleButtons(options=state_list, disabled=False, description='State', button_style='success')


widgets.interactive(update_plot_1, input_1=beh_mod_wid, input_2=state_wid)
```
